Ireland Makes Anglo Irish Revise Bonus Report, Independent Says

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-08-21T12:27:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/ireland-makes-anglo-irish-revise-bonus-report-independent-says.html
Ireland’s Finance Minister  Michael Noonan  has ordered Anglo Irish Bank Corp. to resubmit a report
on bonus payments to senior staff, the Sunday Independent
reported, citing a ministry spokesman.  Noonan wants “clarity” on all extra payments above basic
salaries awarded to employees of the nationalized bank, the
Dublin-based newspaper reported. The final report is scheduled
to be handed in some time in September, according to the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
